And so, Philip,

30:08.407 --> 30:10.342
welcome to the family,
my brother.

30:12.244 --> 30:14.346
Sister.

30:15.414 --> 30:17.383
I love you beyond measure.

30:17.516 --> 30:19.351
WOMAN:
Aw.

30:19.451 --> 30:23.155
The two of you
have been very smiley today.

30:23.255 --> 30:26.192
-And I dig that.
-(people chuckling)

30:26.325 --> 30:29.561
-And, Philip,
yours is very nice,
-(mouthing)

30:29.695 --> 30:32.731
but my sister's...

30:33.765 --> 30:36.402
...my God, if it's not
the same infectious smile

30:36.535 --> 30:38.604
that she had
since we were little kids.

30:39.705 --> 30:42.708
And I'm so happy
that time hasn't changed that.

30:43.709 --> 30:46.445
And I'm really glad
that you broke it back out.

30:49.015 --> 30:51.050
(smacks lips)

30:51.918 --> 30:54.887
I've been thinking
a lot today, um...

30:54.987 --> 30:57.689
about time.

30:57.789 --> 30:59.425
And how, when you're young--

30:59.558 --> 31:01.627
like when you're Jackie's age--

31:01.727 --> 31:04.863
a year is like a fifth
of your existence.

31:04.964 --> 31:08.200
And so maybe
when you're younger,

31:08.300 --> 31:11.403
time seems to move
a little bit slower.

31:12.771 --> 31:15.908
Summer vacation is a lifetime.

31:16.943 --> 31:19.045
But the older we get,

31:19.145 --> 31:22.248
